  "notes": [
    "PMB180 and PMB180B share the same datasheet; package and pinout are identical.",
    "PMB180B adds charge-complete status bit vs. legacy PMB180 and fixes VCC_Pin floating micro-leakage.",
    "Timer16, TM2 PWM, LPWMG, LVDC, charger config, GPC comparator are wired into tool layer.",
    "LPWMG0/1/2 share frequency registers; tools should search for a shared period first, then assign per-channel output.",
    "LVDC threshold range: 1.85V~5.0V, step 0.05V; software poll only, no interrupt/wakeup. Internal detection reads ~0.15V above actual battery during charging.",
    "5V input detection: must check CHG_TEMP.4 && CHG_TEMP.3, not CHG_TEMP.4 alone.",
    "PMB180 (rev 0) full-charge detection needs CHG_CTRL.0, V400_FG, and duration; 4V+ delay rule estimated at 500mAh/hour minimum.",
    "PMB180B CHG_TEMP.1 measured semantics: high=charging, low=complete. Padauk documentation often reversed.",
    "Charge current: 8 levels (50/100/200/250/300/350/400/500mA). CHG_CTRL.0 and CHG_TEMP[4:3] for status decoding.",
    "Watchdog driven by ILRC; options: 8k/16k/64k/256k ILRC cycles.",
    "Datasheet does not indicate ADC resources."
  ]
